laboratory_examinations.findings: Hemoglobin A1c of 8.8%, total cholesterol 246 mg/dL, LDL cholesterol 163 mg/dL, HDL cholesterol 38 mg/dL, triglycerides 209 mg/dL.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Exercise myocardial perfusion imaging stress test
laboratory_examinations.findings: Peak heart rate of 150 beats/min, blood pressure response from 148/92 mm Hg to 168/100 mm Hg, ST depressions with T-wave inversions in leads V2 through V4, left ventricular ejection fraction of 61%, moderate-sized reversible perfusion defect involving the anterior wall.
80% stenosis in the left anterior descending artery, 80% complex lesion in the left circumflex artery, 60% stenosis in proximal right coronary artery.
Elevated residual platelet reactivity with a PRU of 280 U.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up testing in 2 weeks confirmed PRU of 147 U.
